<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>Colleagues,&nbsp;</p> 
<p>On July 15, 2017 we will officially ‘Go-Live’ with using Salesforce.com as the central tool for managing our sales opportunities. Whether that be our regular pipeline reviews and other growth meetings, or managing our metrics and analytics such as win/loss reporting, all will be conducted and managed directly from Salesforce and/or Wave Analytics. This new approach and standard will provide accurate real-time information to both the business and our individual sales team members as we continue to identify and deliver on growth opportunities for Aerospace.</p> 
<p>Given this expectation, please familiarize yourself with the key dates and details outlined below. We encourage you to take full advantage of the following resources in preparation for this pending change in standard procedure:</p> 
<ul> 
<li style="tab-stops: list .5in;"><strong>July 15: Salesforce.com Go-Live Date</strong></li> 
<ul> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.0in;">Open forums and trainings are conducted twice weekly for sales personnel in each vertical. If you need more information, please contact your sales operations focal:</li> 
<ul> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.5in;">ATR <span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">–</span>&nbsp;Louise Maestras <a href="mailto:Louise.Maestas@honeywell.com">Louise.Maestas@honeywell.com</a></li> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.5in;">D&amp;S – Eric Reckman <a href="mailto:Eric.Reckman@Honeywell.com">Eric.Reckman@Honeywell.com</a> &nbsp;</li> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.5in;">BGA&nbsp;<span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">–</span> Mary McBride <a href="mailto:Mary.McBride@honeywell.com" target="_blank" id="">Mary.McBride@honeywell.com</a></li> 
</ul> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.0in;">You are encouraged to engage C&amp;SE representatives to facilitate your operating reviews and be sure to take note of any process and tool changes.</li> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.0in;">Opportunity owners should engage regularly with their Sales Operations Analysts, who are there to provide coaching and support in the health and hygiene of Salesforce data.</li> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.0in;">If you have questions regarding the use of Wave Analytics, please reach out to your Regional C&amp;SE Director.&nbsp;</li> 
</ul> 
</ul> 
<p><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span></p> 
<ul> 
<li style="tab-stops: list .5in;"><strong>July 24: Mandatory Data Clean Up Day</strong></li> 
<ul> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.0in;">Specific to opportunities in Salesforce.com that have been aging in the pipeline with no apparent activity.</li> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.0in;">Sales Operations will be scrutinizing the pipeline for stagnant opportunities and contacting the opportunity owners to determine the appropriate action.</li> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.0in;">Removals from the pipeline will be controlled and measured so one-time adjustments may be made to pipeline growth metrics.</li> 
<li style="tab-stops: list 1.0in;">More details and procedures will be released closer to the Clean Up Day.</li> 
</ul> 
</ul> 
<p>This is an exciting and necessary leap forward in our growth operating system. However, the advantages from these advancements in tools and processes cannot be fully realized without active participation from every single sales team member. Please keep closely aligned with your C&amp;SE representatives to better leverage the available resources.</p> 
<p>Good Selling!</p> 
<p>Mark Winston &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Brad Vatsaas</p> 
<p><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif;">VP Commercial &amp; Sales Excellence &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Director of CRM Infrastructure &amp; Operations</span><br /></p> 
